HEADWORD: Horse-radish
<hw>Horse"-rad`ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant of the genus <gen>Nasturtium</gen> (<spn>Nasturtium
Armoracia</spn>), allied to scurvy grass, having a root of a pungent
taste, much used, when grated, as a condiment and in medicine.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Horse-radish tree</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Moringa</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horserake</ent>⟦br⟧
